you can carry it in one trip.

174
00:08:17,372 --> 00:08:18,707
This is...

175
00:08:18,748 --> 00:08:21,710
I have to go...think.

176
00:08:21,751 --> 00:08:23,628
Uh, okay.

177
00:08:23,712 --> 00:08:26,006
I'll be here.

178
00:08:26,006 --> 00:08:29,509
Hey, Kara. You're not gonna
tell on me, right?

179
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:31,761
It's gonna be okay.

180
00:08:36,182 --> 00:08:37,434
Dr. Gross?

181
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:39,644
Kara! My teacher's pet.

182
00:08:39,686 --> 00:08:41,438
And you know I mean that
in @ good way.

183
00:08:41,438 --> 00:08:45,066
Listen, um, sorry about
running off earlier.

184
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:47,569
When you gotta go, you gotta go.

185
00:08:47,652 --> 00:08:50,697
But that's not really what
you wanna talk about, right?

186
00:08:50,697 --> 00:08:53,158
Well, you know how
you always say

187
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:54,951
that humans will find
the best way?

188
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:57,787
The Founders get credit
for that bit of wisdom.

189
00:08:57,829 --> 00:09:02,083
If someone found a way
that's, uh, different from ours

190
00:09:02,167 --> 00:09:04,044
but seems to work for them,

191
00:09:04,085 --> 00:09:06,046
couldn't that also be
a good way?

192
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:09,924
Ah. You've heard some
Hider preaching, haven't you?

193
00:09:09,966 --> 00:09:11,051
Well, listen, kid.

194
00:09:11,176 --> 00:09:13,470
We tried exploring
the outside world,

195
00:09:13,470 --> 00:09:15,472
and we were almost destroyed!

196
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:17,098
We're the last humans,

197
00:09:17,182 --> 00:09:20,351
so it's our responsibility
to stay here,

198
00:09:20,435 --> 00:09:25,231
and it's your responsibility
to help these misguided Hiders.

199
00:09:25,231 --> 00:09:27,108
Right.

200
00:09:34,991 --> 00:09:36,242
